# MatDAO Coding Standards

## Stack
- Backend: FastAPI (Python 3.11+), Pydantic v2, asyncio
- Frontend: Next.js 14+ (App Router), TypeScript mandatory, Tailwind CSS, Zustand
- DB: PostgreSQL + pgvector
- OCR: Grobid (port 8070) + GLM-OCR (cloud or self-hosted)

## Rules
- Pydantic v2 for ALL data models. Validate API responses at runtime boundary.
- No code comments unless explaining "Why", not "What". Self-documenting names.
- Adapter pattern: one class per API provider in `backend/api/adapters/`.
- Scoring logic ONLY in `backend/services/scoring/`.
- Every automated score links to `origin_snippet` (API JSON or PDF text fragment).
- Search existing patterns before creating new ones ("Search First, Reuse Second").
- Atomic commits: `feat:/fix:/test:/docs:/chore:`. One thing per commit.
- Run verification (pytest/npm test) BEFORE claiming completion.
